// Reciprocal — `1.0/x` where x is a scalar varying lane.  sce-cgc
// lowers this to the NV40 RCP (opcode 0x1A) scalar function-unit
// opcode.  RCP / RSQ can't read a varying directly on the FP SFU
// path, so the emit is a two-step:
//
//   MOVH H0.x, f[COL0];   # promote scalar varying to fp16 H-temp
//   RCPR R0, H0;          # RCP reads H0.x scalar, broadcasts to R0
//
// The MOVH is the same fp16-precision shape used by abs/neg — any
// instruction that sources a register (not a direct INPUT_SRC)
// forces the pre-load and picks fp16 precision to save a cycle.
void main(
    float4 vcol      : COLOR,
    out float4 color : COLOR)
{
    color = 1.0f / vcol.x;
}
